	<h1>Certainly! Here are some instructions to a candidate before
		polling:</h1>

	<h2>1. Familiarize yourself with the rules and regulations:</h2>
	<p>Make sure you are familiar with the rules and regulations set by
		the election authorities. Understand the guidelines regarding
		campaigning, behavior at the polling station, and any specific
		requirements for candidates.</p>

	<h2>2. Bring required identification and documentation:</h2>
	<p>Ensure you have the necessary identification documents as
		specified by the election authorities. This could include a valid ID
		card, candidate registration documents, and any other relevant
		paperwork.</p>

	<h2>3. Know your campaign details:</h2>
	<p>Have a clear understanding of your campaign details, such as
		your assigned candidate number, party affiliation (if applicable), and
		any specific symbols associated with your candidacy.</p>

	<h2>4. Arrive at the polling station on time:</h2>
	<p>Plan your schedule accordingly to arrive at the polling station
		well in advance. This allows you to complete any necessary paperwork
		and set up any campaign materials or signage in designated areas, if
		permitted.</p>

	<h2>5. Maintain decorum and professionalism:</h2>
	<p>Conduct yourself in a professional and respectful manner
		throughout the polling process. Avoid engaging in any activities that
		may be seen as disruptive or against the rules. Treat voters, election
		officials, and other candidates with courtesy and respect.</p>

	<h2>6. Follow campaign guidelines:</h2>
	<p>Adhere to the campaign guidelines set by the election
		authorities. Respect any restrictions on campaign materials,
		canvassing near the polling station, or influencing voters within a
		certain radius of the polling area.</p>

	<h2>7. Support your agents and volunteers:</h2>
	<p>If you have appointed campaign agents or volunteers, ensure they
		are briefed on their roles and responsibilities. Coordinate with them
		to ensure smooth communication and organization during the polling
		process.</p>

	<h2>8. Answer questions from voters:</h2>
	<p>Be prepared to answer questions from voters who may seek
		information about your candidacy, party, or campaign promises. Provide
		accurate and honest responses, avoiding any false or misleading
		information.</p>

	<h2>9. Monitor the voting process:</h2>
	<p>Keep a close eye on the voting process to ensure it is conducted
		fairly and without any irregularities. If you observe any suspicious
		activities or violations, promptly report them to the designated
		election officials or authorities.</p>

	<h2>10. Respect the outcome:</h2>
	<p>Regardless of the election result, accept the outcome gracefully
		and respect the democratic process. Congratulate the winning
		candidate(s) and continue to engage in constructive participation in
		the democratic system.</p>

	<h2>Remember, these instructions are general in nature, and it is
		essential to refer to the specific guidelines provided by the election
		authorities for comprehensive and accurate instructions.</h2>
